# GitHub Actions Rules

## Environment promotion (D-26, ADR-011)
- `dev → staging → prod` chained in ONE workflow
- Use reusable `deploy-common.yml` — SSOT for build/apply/smoke-test
- Prod gate: `environment: production` with
  `required_reviewers: 2` + `wait_timer: 15` + tag-only
- Staging gate: `required_reviewers: 1`

## Permissions + secrets (D-17, D-18)
- `permissions.id-token: write` for Cosign keyless OIDC
- NO static cloud creds — IRSA (AWS) / WI (GCP) only
- `GITHUB_TOKEN` least-privilege (default: contents:read)
- Secrets via `secrets.<NAME>`, never literal; never echoed

## SBOM + signing (D-19, D-30)
For every prod deploy:
1. Build image + tag with git sha
2. `syft` → CycloneDX SBOM
3. `cosign sign --yes` (keyless OIDC)
4. `cosign attest --yes --type cyclonedx` SBOM
5. `kubectl apply` via deploy-common.yml
6. Smoke-test `/ready` before success

## Forbidden
- Standalone `deploy-prod.yml` (D-26)
- `kubectl apply` outside deploy-common.yml
- `uses: org/action@v1` — pin to sha
- Dynamic secret interpolation (`run: eval $SECRET`)

## Audit
Every workflow appends to `ops/audit.jsonl`.
CONSULT/STOP modes open a `audit`-tagged issue.

See `.windsurf/rules/05-github-actions.md`, ADR-011.
